      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(model-auth): resolve secretref-managed custom provider keys from runtime config snapshot",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #92097: Custom providers with `apiKey: \"secretref-managed\"` fail with `503 auth_unavailable` after update to v2026.6.5.\n\n**Root cause**: `resolveUsableCustomProviderApiKey()` returned `null` for non-env secretref markers without consulting the runtime config snapshot where the secrets runtime has already resolved the actual API key.\n\n**Fix**: Add runtime config snapshot fallback before the final `return null`, following the same pattern used by `resolveProviderSyntheticRuntimeAuth()`.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Command**: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/model-auth.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- **Result**: 59/59 passed, including new regression test \"resolves secretref-managed from the runtime config snapshot\"\n\n## Risk\n\nLow — the runtime snapshot is populated by the same trusted secrets runtime that drives `resolveProviderSyntheticRuntimeAuth`. The fallback only activates when the snapshot exists and contains a usable non-marker key.\n\nCloses #92097.\n\n---\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Code <noreply@anthropic.com>",
